  <a name="language_selector"><h1>Language Selector</h1></a>
  <p>
    The language selector window serves multiple purposes. It allows you to select your lnaguage, enable or disable inline translation mode as well as gives you access to the translations application.
    The language selector window can be accessed by clicking on the top language name link at the top left corner of the site. It can also be opened by pressing the CTR+L (control+L) buttons on your keyboard.
    
    Language selector window consists of three major sections: "Your Languages" and "Other Languages" and "Transaltion Application Links. 
    When you first open the language selector, you will notice that English (US) language has been added to "Your Languages" by default. 
    <br><br>
    <%=image_tag("/tr8n/images/help/languages_simple.png")%>
    <br><br>
    
    You can switch a language by clicking on any of the languages in either one of the boxes. Once you select a language of yuor preference, 
    you will see that the site will be displayed in that language. The site may not be fully translated into the language you chose. 
    You can participate in translation of the site by joining the site translators.
    <br><br>
    <%=image_tag("/tr8n/images/help/languages_disabled.png")%>
    <br><br>
    Translating the site can be done in two modes. The first mode allows you to translate the site inline, meaning that you can be viewing any page of the site and translate the phrases on the page.
    You can enable the inline translation mode by clicking on the first link under the languages section. 
    <br><br>
    
    The second way you can translate the site is by going to the Translations application and translating all the phrases of the site in a bulk mode. 
    
  </p>

  <a name="inline_translator"><h1>Inline Translator</h1></a>
  <h2>Translate Phrases Using an Inline Translator</h2>
  <h3>Basics</h3>
  <p>
    Turn on the inline translation mode by clicking on the "Enable inline translations" button in the language selector window. 
    Right-mouse-click on any underlined word to translate the word or to vote on the existing translations.     
  </p>


  <h3>Color coding</h3>
  <p>
    <ul>
      <li>Red line - not translated</li>
      <li>Green line - translated</li>
      <li>Yellow line - fall back language translation</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  
